  "prompt": "Which organ is supplied with most blood.?",
  "response": "The liver receives the most blood supply of any organ in the body. It is unique in its blood supply because it receives blood from two sources: the hepatic artery, which brings oxygen-rich blood from the heart, and the portal vein, which brings nutrient-rich blood from the gastrointestinal tract. This dual blood supply allows the liver to perform its functions effectively, including metabolism, detoxification, and the production of important proteins.",
